news.title: Pay relief to man for not giving auctioned land: Karnataka HC to government
news.para: The govt was also ordered to pay him interest at 10% on the rest of the auction price of Rs 3.1 crore he had deposited with the court and Rs 1 lakh as cost.

news.title: SC issues notice to Gujarat government over appeal against land grabbing law
news.para: This came after the HC on May 9 rejected a slew of petitions challenging the constitutional validity of the law and lifted the stay on proceedings. The HC clarified that the legislation is not repugnant to central laws and therefore did not need presidential assent.

news.title: HC issues contempt notice against Noida authority for not registering Lotus 300 flats
news.para: In its review petition, the Noida Authority said it could not register the flats because the developer was yet to pay Rs 166 crore.

news.title: NPCL team to visit Greater Noida West societies to examine what's causing outages
news.para: NPCL which provides power to Greater Noida West, including the 104 highrises there — will hold inspections in phases. The list of societies to be investigated has been prepared.

news.title: Mumbai: 17 malls get notices for fire safety norm deficiencies
news.para: ​​​A Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation release said 48 of the 68 malls were found to be following fire safety norms during inspections held between May 26 and 30, while 17 malls have got notices for not adhering to these stipulations.

news.title: NCLT initiates insolvency against Jaiprakash Associates, admits ICICI Bank plea
news.para: ​Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL), which is the flagship firm of Jaypee Group, is mainly into construction, cement and hospitality businesses. JAL has sold many cement plants in the last few years to reduce its debt.

news.title: Icra revises domestic steel demand growth rate to 10% for FY25
news.para: It further said that government capex spending was also healthy until February 2024, and other steel-consuming sectors like housing and real estate contributed to the resilient demand thereafter.

news.title: Homeowners & builders pin hopes on European Central Bank's rates cut
news.para: In the west Frankfurt suburbs on a plot wedged between a motorway and a wooded park, excavators are preparing the ground for 400 new apartments.

news.title: Around 18 lakh houses will be constructed under PMAY: Chhattisgarh CM
news.para: Chhattisgarh Chief Minister Vishnu Deo Sai on Monday highlighted the administration's achievements and outlined future plans once the election code of conduct is lifted.

news.title: Embassy REIT raises Rs 1,200 crore debt to acquire business park in Chennai
news.para: This acquisition increases Embassy REIT’s total portfolio by 11% to 50.5 million sq ft. It expects growth from 1.6 million sq ft of on-campus development and 2 million sq ft future development potential.

news.title: Paras Buildtech to invest around Rs 500 crore on Gurugram project
news.para: We are launching a new ultra luxury project in Gurugram. The price of each apartment will be around Rs 9 crore," Kunal Rishi, COO of Paras Buildtech, said.

news.title: Smart road works in Thiruvananthapuram unlikely to meet revised deadline
news.para: On Friday night, a significant sewerage line burst in the Vazhuthacaud area, halting the work compounding the challenges faced by the contractors.

news.title: Buildings’ survey afoot in Goa, tax & NOC status on radar too
news.para: The current TCP zoning will be documented in the exercise. Details on construction licences from the local authorities will also be gleaned from the data.

news.title: Bengaluru: RK Township residents express concerns about their safety during monsoon
news.para: Approximately 4,000 families residing in and around RK Township at Yarandahalli express concerns about their safety during the monsoon season.

news.title: Properties worth Rs 1.17 lakh crore sold by 18 listed realty firms in FY24
news.para: Major real estate developers in India, including Godrej Properties, Prestige Estates Projects, and DLF, achieved significant sales bookings in the last fiscal year driven by strong demand for residential properties, especially luxury homes.

news.title: JM Financial to fund realty projects through AIF & syndications
news.para: JM Financial Group shifts to funding real estate projects through AIF route and syndications, transitioning to investment banking-led distribution. Vishal Kampani, non-executive vice chairman, announces strategic AIF for land and approval financing.

news.title: Home prices in Australia continue to climb, Sydney back at record high
news.para: CoreLogic Research Director Tim Lawless said low supply had kept Australian housing prices largely insulated from the combined effect of high interest rates, cost of living pressures and deeply pessimistic consumer sentiment.

news.title: High-rise buildings in Mumbai to increase 34% by 2030: Anarock
news.para: Mumbai metropolitan region currently has 361 high-rise towers of over 40 floors each. Of these, 154 have already been completed and over 207 are scheduled to be completed between 2024 and 2030.

news.title: Goa CM blames consultant for delay in smart city works
news.para: The deadline was given by state govt to the Imagine Panaji Smart City Development Ltd (IPSCDL) for completing the ongoing works in the city.

news.title: Karnataka HC bans commercial parking on residential empty plots
news.para: ​The court has instructed the municipal body, Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP), to submit a detailed project report on the methodology for implementing Parking policy 2.0. The BBMP has been given six weeks to submit the report.
